<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><refentry version="5.0-subset Scilab" xml:id="imnlmfilt" xml:lang="en" xmlns="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><refnamediv><refname>imnlmfilt</refname><refpurpose>Apply fast non-local-means denoising.</refpurpose></refnamediv><refsynopsisdiv><title>Syntax</title><synopsis>out = imnlmfilt(image); out = imnlmfilt(image, h, hColor, templateWindowSize, searchWindowSize)</synopsis></refsynopsisdiv><refsection><title>Parameters</title><variablelist><varlistentry><term>image</term><listitem><para>Input uint8 grayscale or RGB image.</para></listitem></varlistentry><varlistentry><term>h, hColor</term><listitem><para>Positive luminance and color filter strengths.</para></listitem></varlistentry><varlistentry><term>templateWindowSize, searchWindowSize</term><listitem><para>Positive odd patch and search sizes.</para></listitem></varlistentry></variablelist></refsection><refsection><title>Description</title><para><function>imnlmfilt</function> is a MATLAB-style compatibility entry point for <function>imdenoise</function>, which exposes OpenCV fast non-local-means denoising.</para></refsection><refsection><title>Examples</title><programlisting><![CDATA[image = imread(fullpath(getIPCVpath() + "/images/baboon.png")); out = imnlmfilt(image, 5, 5, 7, 21); imshow(out);]]></programlisting></refsection><refsection role="see also"><title>See also</title><simplelist type="inline"><member><link linkend="imdenoise">imdenoise</link></member><member><link linkend="immedianfilt">immedianfilt</link></member></simplelist></refsection><refsection><title>Authors</title><simplelist type="vert"><member>Tan Chin Luh</member></simplelist></refsection><refsection><title>History</title><informaltable border="1"><tr><td>Version</td><td>Description</td></tr><tr><td>5.0.0</td><td>Compatibility entry point introduced in development Step 3.</td></tr></informaltable></refsection></refentry>
